Create a modern Material Design + Bootstrap hero component named MTK-hero.

ASSUMPTIONS
- Use Bootstrap 5
- Use vanilla JavaScript only
- No frameworks
- No shadows, no borders, no rounded corners
- Follow Material Design motion principles
- Component must be fully JSON-driven
- Component must be load-order safe

CORE REQUIREMENTS
- Component name: MTK-hero
- Full page width
- Fully responsive
- Background color: #fafafa
- Uses a Bootstrap container (not container-fluid)

LAYOUT
- Two-column layout
- Left side class: .MTK-hero-lhs
- Right side class: .MTK-hero-rhs
- Desktop order:
  - Left: Card with title and description
  - Right: Image
- Mobile order:
  - Right side (image) appears first
  - Left side (card) appears second

CARD REQUIREMENTS
- Card is on the left side
- Card background is the same as MTK-hero background (#fafafa)
- No border
- No box shadow
- Title and description only

IMAGE REQUIREMENTS
- Image is on the right side
- Responsive image
- Uses img-fluid

DATA AND CONFIGURATION
- All content must come from JSON
- JSON source is window.app.hero
- JSON must be defined in a separate file named MTK-hero.config.js
- JSON supports:
  - title
  - description
  - image
  - lhsCol (Bootstrap col-md-??)
  - rhsCol (Bootstrap col-md-??)

FILES TO CREATE
1. MTK-hero.config.js (JSON config)
2. MTK-hero.html (optional static structure support)
3. MTK-hero.scss
4. MTK-hero.css (compiled from SCSS)
5. MTK-hero.js (full, production-ready)

JAVASCRIPT BEHAVIOR
- Must wait for #MTK-hero to appear in the DOM before running
- Must wait for window.app.hero to exist before rendering
- Must dynamically inject HTML if #MTK-hero is empty
- Must not throw errors if load order changes
- Must wait for .animate-fade-up elements before triggering animations
- Must use an IIFE to avoid polluting global scope

ANIMATION
- Material Design style fade-up animation
- Use class .animate-fade-up
- Animation triggers by adding .active
- Animation applied only after DOM + data are ready

OUTPUT REQUIREMENTS
- Provide complete code for:
  - JSON config
  - HTML
  - SCSS
  - CSS
  - JavaScript
- Code must be clean, readable, and production-ready
- Do not use em dashes
- Do not omit error handling
- Do not assume script load order
